00:10:50.570 --> 00:10:53.570
It Is the highest form
of humor that you

00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:54.820
can possibly do.

00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:58.090
And try to think about this
every single day of your life.

00:10:58.090 --> 00:11:00.450
Any time you make a mistake or
you did something wrong,

00:11:00.450 --> 00:11:04.650
instead of saying, oh, stupid,
say, hey, this is fun.

00:11:04.650 --> 00:11:06.390
Let me give you an example.

00:11:06.390 --> 00:11:08.450
When I was a young
man growing up--

00:11:08.450 --> 00:11:10.540
I grew up in the
United States--

00:11:10.540 --> 00:11:12.380
and I had a dream.

00:11:12.380 --> 00:11:14.660
And that dream was I wanted to
be a radio and television

00:11:14.660 --> 00:11:17.610
announcer, you know, the guy
that sits in front of the

00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:21.240
camera and delivers the news,
like a news [INAUDIBLE],

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.836
whatever it is.

00:11:22.836 --> 00:11:26.330
And so I went to school in
Boston, to a school called

00:11:26.330 --> 00:11:29.370
Emerson College, where
they taught theater.

00:11:29.370 --> 00:11:32.775
And one of the subjects I
learned was broadcasting,

00:11:32.775 --> 00:11:36.540
where they taught you how to
speak like a radio announcer,

00:11:36.540 --> 00:11:38.230
an American radio announcer.

00:11:38.230 --> 00:11:40.220
And you had to speak something
like this.

00:11:40.220 --> 00:11:49.250
And now, back to our show,
"The Flying Chicken." I

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:53.360
practiced this so much, and I
got into this voice so much, I

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:55.510
couldn't get out.

00:11:55.510 --> 00:11:56.220
It was embarrassing.

00:11:56.220 --> 00:11:57.050
I would go to a party.

00:11:57.050 --> 00:12:01.440
Hello, John, how are you, go
home, hello, darling, how

00:12:01.440 --> 00:12:02.690
about a hug?

00:12:04.996 --> 00:12:10.350
I finally got a job at
WAPI TV and Radio

00:12:10.350 --> 00:12:11.710
in Birmingham, Alabama.

00:12:11.710 --> 00:12:13.550
Anybody know where Birmingham,
Alabama is?

00:12:13.550 --> 00:12:18.490
It's down south, next to
Georgia, Louisiana, Texas.

00:12:18.490 --> 00:12:20.060
And I was very excited.

00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:24.470
My first day at work, I sat
in front of the camera.

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:27.310
I had to go on the
air at 8 o'clock.

00:12:27.310 --> 00:12:30.930
It is now one minute to 8:00.

00:12:30.930 --> 00:12:32.430
The lights come down
in the studio.

00:12:32.430 --> 00:12:35.330
And a light goes
up on the door.

00:12:35.330 --> 00:12:36.660
It says, on the air.

00:12:36.660 --> 00:12:39.860
And then, there's a red
light on the camera.

00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:41.180
And the camera comes
in slowly.

00:12:41.180 --> 00:12:44.280
And there's this woman who has
earphones, and she goes like

00:12:44.280 --> 00:12:46.782
this to me, [POINTING].

00:12:46.782 --> 00:12:48.240
And she points to me.

00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:50.730
And then the music starts,
you know the music, the

00:12:50.730 --> 00:12:54.050
broadcasting music, da, da
da, da, da, da, da, da.

00:12:54.050 --> 00:12:55.470
And I looked at the camera.

00:12:55.470 --> 00:12:56.770
And I said this.

00:12:56.770 --> 00:12:59.160
I said, good evening--

00:12:59.160 --> 00:13:00.950
you know, that voice--

00:13:00.950 --> 00:13:05.930
and here is the news, read
to you by Leonard Ravich.

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:08.900
Oh, I was delighted.

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:10.410
I had achieved my dream.

00:13:10.410 --> 00:13:13.020
I had a dream job, you know.

00:13:13.020 --> 00:13:14.900
The next day I came
to the studio.

00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.950
And I noticed that people's
reactions to me were a little

00:13:16.950 --> 00:13:18.320
different, that people
were going like this,

00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:19.070
[SNICKERING], like that.

00:13:19.070 --> 00:13:20.570
I go, what happened?

00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:23.820
I was receiving mail and
telephone calls.

00:13:23.820 --> 00:13:27.300
People wanted to speak
to Leonard Garbage.

00:13:27.300 --> 00:13:30.330
I said Ravich, they
heard garbage.

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:32.880
I was getting telephone calls.

00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:37.710
And people wanted to speak to
Leonard Rubbish, Rabbit.

00:13:37.710 --> 00:13:39.720
Is Mr. Rabbit there, you know?

00:13:39.720 --> 00:13:45.100
One person even sent mail to
Leonard Ravage, R-A-V-A-G-E,

00:13:45.100 --> 00:13:46.040
which means to--

00:13:46.040 --> 00:13:49.300
I looked it up-- it means
to rape and pillage.

00:13:49.300 --> 00:13:51.750
And I am completely innocent
of all wrongdoing.

00:13:54.530 --> 00:13:58.390
So I got an hour
before I go on.

00:13:58.390 --> 00:13:59.440
And I'm nervous.

00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:05.080
And the cortisol, you know, and
the stress, what do I do?

00:14:05.080 --> 00:14:08.240
So I thought, I'll
change my name.

00:14:08.240 --> 00:14:10.130
Leonard part, I'll keep
the Leonard part.

00:14:10.130 --> 00:14:10.550
That's OK.

00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:13.840
But I got to change
the garbage.

00:14:13.840 --> 00:14:16.980
OK, so Leonard Ra-- you know,
something with a R-A--

00:14:16.980 --> 00:14:18.390
Reynolds, no.

00:14:18.390 --> 00:14:20.310
Leonard Roberts, no.

00:14:20.310 --> 00:14:21.590
Leonard--

00:14:21.590 --> 00:14:22.890
I got it--

00:14:22.890 --> 00:14:23.963
Raymond.

00:14:23.963 --> 00:14:26.330
OK, that's cool, huh?

00:14:26.330 --> 00:14:28.210
Leonard Raymond.

00:14:28.210 --> 00:14:29.710
OK, so I went to everybody's
office.

00:14:29.710 --> 00:14:31.740
I'm no longer Leonard Ravich.

00:14:31.740 --> 00:14:34.060
I'm Leonard Raymond.

00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:37.810
Everybody looked up and
said, thank God.

00:14:37.810 --> 00:14:40.050
Got in front of the camera,
one minute to 8:00.

00:14:40.050 --> 00:14:41.080
Lights come down.

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:43.820
Light goes up on the door,
says on the air.

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:46.480
The television camera
comes in, red light.

00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:49.050
And there's this producer who
goes like this to me,

00:14:49.050 --> 00:14:51.460
[COUNTING DOWN WITH FINGERS].

00:14:51.460 --> 00:14:54.450
And I hear the music,
da,da,da,da,da,da,da,da.

00:14:54.450 --> 00:14:56.580
And it happened just
like this.

00:14:56.580 --> 00:15:00.080
I looked at the camera and I
said, in that broadcasting

00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:04.280
voice, good evening, and here
is the news, read to you by

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:05.580
Leonard [MUMBLING].

00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:14.770
I became the first radio and
television announcer in the

00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:20.650
history of the United States who
forgot his name during a

00:15:20.650 --> 00:15:22.900
live broadcast.

00:15:22.900 --> 00:15:25.900
But you had to be spontaneous,
because it's air time.

00:15:25.900 --> 00:15:28.710
And it costs a lot of money, so
you have to say something

00:15:28.710 --> 00:15:29.130
right away.

00:15:29.130 --> 00:15:32.372
So I said, I forgot my name,
but here is the news.

00:15:32.372 --> 00:15:33.216
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:33.216 --> 00:15:34.466
LEONARD RAVICH: Washington.

00:15:38.780 --> 00:15:43.040
If I'm not mistaken, I can see
you laughing and hear you.

00:15:43.040 --> 00:15:47.260
The thing is, are you laughing
at me or are you laughing--

00:15:47.260 --> 00:15:48.045
AUDIENCE: With.

00:15:48.045 --> 00:15:49.500
LEONARD RAVICH: --with me?

00:15:49.500 --> 00:15:52.200
Because when you laugh at
yourself, when you make fun of

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:54.970
yourself, you bring people
closer to you.

00:15:54.970 --> 00:15:57.170
It's called intimacy.

00:15:57.170 --> 00:16:00.632
My interpretation of intimacy
is in-to-me-see.

00:16:00.632 --> 00:16:03.730
And the more of you I show
of me, and I show you my

00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:06.680
mistakes, I bring you
closer to me.

00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:09.840
And this makes for meaningful
relationships.

00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:14.280
So the first tool is laugh
at yourself and breathe.

00:16:14.280 --> 00:16:15.820
Now, I want you to take
something back.

00:16:15.820 --> 00:16:18.960
I don't want you just to
experience this in your mind.

00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:20.670
I want you to experience
it in your body.

00:16:20.670 --> 00:16:24.150
So we're going to do something
right now, an experiment.

00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:26.360
Now, experiments are scary.

00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:27.260
And why are they scary?

00:16:27.260 --> 00:16:29.390
Because you leave your
comfort zone.

00:16:29.390 --> 00:16:32.260
Because you're going to do
something that you don't know.

00:16:32.260 --> 00:16:33.690
So you have two choices.

00:16:33.690 --> 00:16:36.980
One is not to take part
in this experiment.

00:16:36.980 --> 00:16:40.270
The other is to walk
into the fear.

00:16:40.270 --> 00:16:44.940
Because when you are afraid and
do it anyway, you learn

00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:47.130
something new about yourself.

00:16:47.130 --> 00:16:49.300
So you have a choice.

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:51.900
If you're uncomfortable and
you don't want to do

00:16:51.900 --> 00:16:52.550
it, don't do it.

00:16:52.550 --> 00:16:54.760
If you're uncomfortable and
you still want to do it,

00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:56.530
remember that you're going
to learn something.

00:16:56.530 --> 00:16:59.500
Those people who are going to
participate with me, do this.

00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:02.640
Raise your finger in the air.

00:17:02.640 --> 00:17:05.750
And then you bring it down over
here in front of you.

00:17:05.750 --> 00:17:07.589
And you do this,
[POINTING AT SELF].

00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:10.130
Now, in about 30 seconds,
you're going to

00:17:10.130 --> 00:17:11.702
be laughing at yourself.

00:17:11.702 --> 00:17:14.720
You see, you're already
doing it.

00:17:14.720 --> 00:17:16.482
OK, so smile.

00:17:16.482 --> 00:17:17.650
And when I count to three--

00:17:17.650 --> 00:17:20.599
I'm going to say 1, 2, 3-- you
go, ha, ha ha, ha, ha, ha.

00:17:20.599 --> 00:17:22.190
OK, 1, 2, 3, and, ha, ha, ha,
ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

00:17:25.280 --> 00:17:29.930
1, 2, 3, and ha,ha, ha,ha, ha,
ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

00:17:29.930 --> 00:17:33.740
1, 2, 3, and ha, ha, ha,
ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:36.470
OK, make believe you've got
a flower in your fingers.

00:17:36.470 --> 00:17:38.280
Take the flower, put
